l.","Once chilled, fill each pie shell with cooled beef mixture.","Using a rolling pin, roll out iced puff pastry on a ThermoMat or floured work surface to a 5 mm thickness. Cut into 6 discs, large enough to form the top of each pie. Place 1 disc on top of each pie and seal by pressing around the edges.","Slice across top of each pie to form a slit in the pastry then bake for 30 - 35 minutes (200°C) or until pastry is golden and puffy. Allow to cool slightly before removing from tray. Serve pies warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Shortcrust pastry","content":["200 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","100 g butter, cut into pieces, chilled","¼ tsp salt","50 - 60 g water, chilled"]},{"title":"Iced puff pastry","content":["90 g ice cubes","180 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces, frozen","200 g plain flour","1 ½ tsp salt"]},{"title":"Pie filling","content":["butter, for greasing","2 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","2 garlic cloves","1 brown onion (approx. 180 g), cut into halves","2 tbsp olive oil","1 tbsp cornflour","500 g beef fillet, cut into pieces (2 cm)","2 tbsp Worcestershire sauce","2 tbsp soy sauce","1 tbsp Vegemite®","100 - 120 g button mushrooms, cut into thin slices","½ tsp ground black pepper, to taste"]}],"id":"r68521","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-KZfihTmHWJc\/XZQuhbe6FII\/AAAAAAAAcUI\/gpy8U0aI1gwFmkrFz0aGl9vBil0TehutACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1QzcUjBMLj3csX89.png","title":"Aussie meat pies","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"41 g","fat":"29 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"55 g","calories":"2729 kJ \/ 650 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ThermoMat, plastic wrap, Texas-size 6 hole muffin tray, rolling pin, refrigerator, freezer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve meat pies with tomato ketchup.","Roll out, wrap and freeze any leftover pastry to use at a later date."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","2h","6 portions"]}